"https://api.github.com/users/mdibaiee/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mdibaiee/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mdibaiee/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mdibaiee/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mdibaiee/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mdibaiee/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mdibaiee/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mdibaiee/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/mdibaiee/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}], "milestone": null, "comments": 4, "created_at": "2020-09-19T19:31:21Z", "updated_at": "2022-01-16T20:27:49Z", "closed_at": "2022-01-16T20:27:49Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Inspired by #76914. Currently, we have a lint in `rustc` for types that should *always* be passed by value. Usually, these types are thin wrappers around references, so there is no benefit to an extra layer of indirection. However, this lint uses a hard-coded list of (diagnostic) names (currently `Ty` and `TyCtxt`). We should use an attribute (e.g. `#[rustc_pass_by_value]`) to control this. Note that `Ty` is a type alias, not a `struct`.\r\n\r\nThis is worthwhile because there are more widely used types that are merely a wrapper around a reference (e.g. `ty::Predicate`). One could also imagine crates in the ecosystem that also do a lot of interning might take advantage of this.\r\n\r\ncc @lcnr \n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_START -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_START -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_DATA_START$${\"user\":\"mdibaiee\"}$$TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_DATA_END -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_END -->\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_END -->", "closed_by": {"login": "bors", "id": 3372342, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMzNzIzNDI=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3372342?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://a